      <hedline>
        <hl1>Typing Rhythms an Old Idea</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kurt Schuster letter notes a precedent for use of typing rhythms as a means of validating the identity of a person doing the typing (June 29 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The idea of using typing rhythms as a means of validating the identity of the person doing the typing is not new (''New Encryption Strategy: Typing Rhythm,'' June 29). It was used as a plot device in a short story titled ''Mousetrap.'' In the story the theft of the source code for a computer was foiled when the person trying to steal the files did not type in the stolen password the same way its owner would.</p>
        <p>KURT SCHUSTER  Wayne, N.J.</p>
      </block>
